subject: College Athletics
Hockey, Ice
Women
lead_paragraph: Kim Martin stopped 28 shots Saturday to lead Minnesota Duluth to a 4-0 victory over Wisconsin and its first N.C.A.A. women’s hockey championship since 2003.
